Figure 3a shows the Nyquist plots obtained from the EIS
contact. Two semicircles can be clearly observed: one smaller at
high frequencies and the other semicircle much larger at low
frequencies. Several studies done by Buschmann et al.
support the fact that this ï¬rst semicircle can
be assigned as the sum of the bulk and grain boundary
responses and, therefore, as the total Li-ion conductivity of the
material. The second semicircle is assigned to the response due
to the reversible incorporation of Li ions from the LZLGO
material into the Li metal. This assignment is supported by
blocking electrode measurements where the second semicircle
in the Li electrodes is replaced by a low frequency tail due to
the capacitive behavior of this blocking electrode. Figure 3b
shows the Nyquist plots for a LZLGO_150 composition pellet
measured using either Li-blocking electrodes made of Ag or Li
electrodes. It can be seen that the second semicircle in the Li
electrode measurement corresponds to the low frequency tail
observed with the Ag-blocking electrodes conï¬rming the
assignment of this second semicircle. As a consequence Li-
